  "body": "## Background\r\n\r\nI recently posted [this question](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/83742/is-it-possible-to-filter-pendingtransactions) on `ethereum.stackexchange` and after solving my own question I thought that I'd raise the issue to have filter functionality included in the `go-ethereum` RPC calls.\r\n\r\nCurrently OpenEthereum has this functionality.\r\n\r\n[`parity_pendingtransactions`](https://openethereum.github.io/wiki/JSONRPC-parity-module.html#parity_pendingtransactions)\r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\r\n  \"method\":\"parity_pendingTransactions\",\r\n  \"params\":[\r\n    null,\r\n    {\r\n      \"to\": { \"eq\": \"0xe8b2d01ffa0a15736b2370b6e5064f9702c891b6\" }\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"id\":1\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't see introducing filter fields to the parameters to the `go-ethereum` `eth_pendingTransactions` JSON_RPC method would introduce any kind of breaking change, as the change is an extension of existing functionality.\r\n\r\n## Proposal\r\n\r\nExtend the functionality of the `eth_pendingTransactions` JSON_RPC method, so that the method can accept parameters used for filtering transactions in the pending pool.\r\n\r\n## Benefits\r\n\r\n- Reduce the amount of bandwidth consumed by a client only interested in a small subset of the current pending transaction pool.\r\n- Reduce the amount of data parsing a client needs to do to find the relevant data.",
